    <example id="exam-00008">
    <title>Payments for Consolidated Student Loans</title>
    <exercise id="exer-00015">
    <problem id="prob-00015">
    <para id="para-00050">Brianna consolidates her student loans, some federal and some private, into a single refinanced student loan with a principal of $27,800. The interest rate that Brianna received was 8.375%. If Brianna’s new term is 15 years, how much are her payments per month?</para>
    </problem>
    <solution id="sol-00008">
    <para id="para-00051">The principal is <emphasis effect="italic">P</emphasis> = $27,800 and the rate is <emphasis effect="italic">r</emphasis> = 0.08375. Since the payments are monthly, <emphasis effect="italic">n</emphasis> =12. The loan term is for 15 years, so <emphasis effect="italic">t</emphasis> = 15. years. Substituting those values into <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mrow><mi>p</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo>×</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></math> and calculating gives a monthly payment of
    <equation id="eq-00005" xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><mtable columnspacing="0.3em"><mtr><mtd columnalign="right"><mi>p</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>t</mi></mtd><mtd columnalign="center"><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd columnalign="left"><mfrac><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo>×</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd columnalign="right"/><mtd columnalign="center"><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd columnalign="left"><mfrac><mrow><mtext>$</mtext><mn>27,800</mn><mo>×</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>0.08375</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>12</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0.08375</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>12</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0.08375</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>12</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd columnalign="right"/><mtd columnalign="center"><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd columnalign="left"><mfrac><mrow><mtext>$</mtext><mn>6,200</mn><mo>×</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>0.0069791</mn><mover accent="true"><mn>6</mn><mo stretchy="true">¯</mo></mover><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1.0069791</mn><mover accent="true"><mn>6</mn><mo stretchy="true">¯</mo></mover><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>180</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1.0069791</mn><mover accent="true"><mn>6</mn><mo stretchy="true">¯</mo></mover><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>180</mn></mrow></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd columnalign="right"/><mtd columnalign="center"><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd columnalign="left"><mfrac><mrow><mtext>$</mtext><mn>678.477992464</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2.49693370968</mn></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd columnalign="right"/><mtd columnalign="center"><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd columnalign="left"><mtext>$</mtext><mn>271.73</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></equation></para>
